</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Origin: Lacks dated colophon ; likely copied in Egypt in the late 1930s and bound for James Heyworth-Dunne (d.1974).</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Former shelfmark: Mich. Isl. Ms. temp. no. 122</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Binding: Boards covered in dark green cloth with dark green leather over spine (quarter binding) ; pastedowns and flyleaves in wove paper printed with a floral vegetal pattern in green ; spine gold-stamped with title and decorative accents over raised bands "الطهارة والتهذيب | ابن مسكويه| J.H.D." ; sewn in white thread over two recessed cords ; stuck-on endbands (blue and white stripe) ; overall in fairly good condition.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Support: Wove paper both lined / ruled and unruled ; inner flyleaves in laid paper.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Decoration: Text executed entirely in red ink.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Script: Ruqʻah ; quick, compact hand in thin to bold line (line thickness changes) ; serifless and freely ligatured with mainly closed counters, effect of inclination to the left and of words descending to baseline, pointing somewhat careless and in strokes rather than distinct dots.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Layout: Written in 10-16 lines per page.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Collation: ii, IV (8), 2 VI(32), VIII (48), X+1 (69), VIII (85), VII (99), ii ; pages between sections (corresponding mainly to gatherings) left blank, with some serving as 'title pages' (see pp.19, 43, 67, 99, 141, 173) ; catchwords present ; pagination in pencil, Western numerals, supplied during digitization (includes inner flyleaves).</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Explicit: "شفاءها بالاستنباط مما قد ذكرناه والله يتولي هداه وليكن هذا اخر ما اردنا تلخيصه من متن تهذيب الاخلاق وتطهير الاعراق والسلام على من اتبع الهدى آمين"</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Incipit: "اللهم انا نتوجه اليك ونسعي نحوك ونجاهد نفوسنا في طاعتك ونركب الصراط المستقيم الذي نهجته لنا الى مرضاتك ... وبعد فالغرض من وضع هذه الرسالة ان نبين الاخلاق التي هي اسباب السعادة ..."</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Title supplied by cataloguer from close on p.199.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Ms. codex.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="510" ind1="4" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Brockelmann, C. GAL,</subfield><subfield code="c">I 342 ; S I 582 ff.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="520" ind1="8" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Careful copy of an abridgment (perhaps by the copyist) of Abū ʻAlī Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad Miskawayh’s (d. 1030) treatise on ethics, Tahdhīb al-akhlāq wa-taṭhīr al-aʻrāq.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="538" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Mode of access: Internet.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="541" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Acquired in the Fall of 1950.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="546" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Arabic.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="561" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">On upper pastedown, label with ex libris of James Heyworth-Dunne (d.1974), stamped with inventory number, "Ex Libris | J. Heyworth-Dunne | D. Lit. (London) | No. 7917" ; UM Library inscription on p.5 "Dunning | Heyworth-Dunne | 6-13-51 | 71955" ; numerous glosses as well as marginal and interlinear corrections in red ink and pencil.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="650" ind1=" " ind2="0"><subfield code="a">Manuscripts, Arabic</subfield><subfield code="z